FMOLS and DOLS represent sophisticated time-series techniques employed for cointegration analysis, effectively tackling challenges such as serial correlation and endogeneity. FMOLS addresses the issues of serial correlation and endogenous regressors by making adjustments to the estimator’s bias, whereas DOLS utilizes leads and lags of the first-differenced regressor to mitigate potential endogeneity and serial correlation. These methods outperform traditional OLS as they yield more consistent and efficient estimates when addressing non-stationary, cointegrated time series, thus enhancing the reliability of long-term relationship analysis.6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
